Class OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<T,U>

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ox.comlab.diadem.oxpath.parser.visitor.OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<T,U>
All Implemented Interfaces:
OXPathParserVisitor
Direct Known Subclasses:
PAATEval_Visitor, PAATEvalVisitor, PrePAATVisitor, PrintVisitor
public abstract class OXPathVisitorGenericAdaptor<T,U>
extends java.lang.Object
implements OXPathParserVisitor

Wrapper allowing generic specification of Visitor classes for the OXPath AST. Used to General contract for this class is that all accept calls pass data of type T and return output of type U. This is not safe; if the contract is broken, the class will break hard with a CastClassException. Use only for convenience and test thoroughly. Implement the visitNode methods and call this.accept(node,data) instead of node.jjtAccept(visitor,data) in order to avoid casting in visitor implementations.

Author:
AndrewJSel
